<section id="importing-and-exporting-database-preferences" version="5.0" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"
                                                                         xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
                                                                         xmlns:xl="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" >
  <title>Importing and exporting database preferences</title>
  <anchor role="helpid" id="databaseConnectionConfigurationDialogContextId">Database connection preferences</anchor>
  <para>
    You can export and import your database preferences for the ITE.
    This makes migrating to new versions easier, as you do not have
    to reenter any database preferences.
  </para>
  <para>
    To export your database preferences:
  </para>
  <orderedlist>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        Select:
        
        <para>
          <emphasis role="menuPath">File</emphasis>--&gt;<emphasis role="menuPath">Export</emphasis>
        </para>
        
        from the main menu in the ITE.
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        In the dialog that appears, select:
        <emphasis>General/Preferences</emphasis> and click
        ”<emphasis>Next</emphasis>”.
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        Select the <emphasis>Database Connections</emphasis> option
        and browse to a place in the file system where you want the
        preferences to be saved.
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        Click ”<emphasis>Finish</emphasis>”.
      </para>
    </listitem>
  </orderedlist>
  <para>
    To import your database preferences:
  </para>
  <orderedlist>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        Select:
        
        <para>
          <emphasis role="menuPath">File</emphasis>--&gt;<emphasis role="menuPath">Import</emphasis>
        </para>
        
        from the main menu in the ITE.
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        In the dialog that appears, select:
        <emphasis>General/Preferences</emphasis> and click
        ”<emphasis>Next</emphasis>”.
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        Browse to the preference file you wish to import.
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        Select the <emphasis>Database Connections</emphasis> option
        and click ”<emphasis>Finish</emphasis>”.
      </para>
    </listitem>
  </orderedlist>
</section>